Getting files closed on errors should look something like:<p><pre><code>    file, err := os.Open(filename)
    if err != nil {
        // handle the error however you see fit
    }
    defer file.Close()
    // continue working, knowing that file.Close() will be called when the surrounding function returns
</code></pre>
See: <a href="http://golang.org/doc/effective_go.html#defer" rel="nofollow">http://golang.org/doc/effective_go.html#defer</a>
